1
00:00:01,006 --> 00:00:02,465
SENATOR: <i>John F Walker,</i>

2
00:00:02,549 --> 00:00:06,636
<i>you are hereby stripped of your title
and authority as Captain America,</i>

3
00:00:06,720 --> 00:00:08,180
<i>effective immediately.</i>

4
00:00:10,807 --> 00:00:12,058
Everybody, grab what you can.

5
00:00:12,142 --> 00:00:14,019
DOVICH: <i>Power Broker will
catch up with us eventually.</i>

6
00:00:14,102 --> 00:00:17,063
- BUCKY: I've been making amends.
- No, you were avenging.

7
00:00:17,147 --> 00:00:19,900
You want to climb out
of that hell you're in, do the work.

8
00:00:20,775 --> 00:00:22,485
ISAIAH: She died while I was in jail.

9
00:00:22,569 --> 00:00:27,866
They will never let a Black man
be Captain America.

10
00:00:27,949 --> 00:00:30,619
SARAH: <i>You gonna let Isaiah Bradley
get in your head?</i>

11
00:00:30,702 --> 00:00:34,456
If I was in his shoes,
I'd probably feel the exact same way.

12
00:00:34,539 --> 00:00:37,584
But what would be the point
of all the pain and sacrifice

13
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:40,128
<i>if I wasn't willing to stand up
and keep fightin'?</i>

14
00:00:40,212 --> 00:00:42,005
We will ensure the GRC vote never happens.

15
00:00:42,088 --> 00:00:44,507
- I'm only here to kill the Falcon.
- You'll get your chance.

16
00:00:44,591 --> 00:00:46,426
Tonight, we go to battle.

17
00:00:53,767 --> 00:00:54,851
(MUSIC PLAYING)

18
00:01:38,937 --> 00:01:40,021
KARLI: <i>The movement is ready.</i>

19
00:01:41,523 --> 00:01:42,899
<i>They're not going to stop.</i>

20
00:01:43,775 --> 00:01:45,068
<i>Not unless we make them.</i>

21
00:01:47,279 --> 00:01:48,280
<i>It's time.</i>

22
00:01:55,328 --> 00:01:57,163
REPORTER: (OVER TV) <i>We have breaking news.</i>

23
00:01:57,247 --> 00:01:59,916
<i>There's a complete lockdown
at the GRC meeting in Lower Manhattan</i>

24
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,752
<i>where authorities are saying
they're tracking multiple threats</i>

25
00:02:02,836 --> 00:02:06,923
<i>from groups seeking to stop
the GRC's vote on global resettlement.</i>

26
00:02:07,007 --> 00:02:09,217
<i>- There is a no-fly zone in effect...</i>
- (SIREN WAILING)

27
00:02:09,301 --> 00:02:11,469
<i>...and the NYPD has the area secured
for the moment.</i>

28
00:02:11,553 --> 00:02:13,471
<i>Everyone is urged to stay clear.</i>

29
00:02:13,555 --> 00:02:15,098
( INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

30
00:02:25,567 --> 00:02:27,569
SAM: (OVER RADIO) <i>I’m almost there.</i>

31
00:02:28,570 --> 00:02:30,113
What's the plan?

32
00:02:30,196 --> 00:02:31,281
SAM: <i>Karli's gotta be close.</i>

33
00:02:31,364 --> 00:02:33,742
<i>- Keep your eyes open.</i>
- Well, it could be anybody.

34
00:02:33,825 --> 00:02:34,868
OFFICER: Sergeant Barnes.

35
00:02:38,038 --> 00:02:40,707
SAM: <i>And by the way,
I called in some backup.</i>

36
00:02:40,790 --> 00:02:43,376
Excuse me, sir.
Are you supposed to be here?

37
00:02:47,505 --> 00:02:48,506
It's me.

38
00:02:48,590 --> 00:02:51,968
- Sharon, what the hell are you doing here?
- Relax. No one's looking for me here.

39
00:02:52,052 --> 00:02:53,803
- SAM: <i>Is that Sharon?</i>
- Unfortunately.

40
00:02:53,887 --> 00:02:56,014
Hey, Sam.
I thought I'd get the band back together.

41
00:02:56,097 --> 00:02:58,683
SAM: <i>Thank you.
You're risking a lot coming here.</i>

42
00:02:58,767 --> 00:03:01,227
I hear pardons
aren't all they're cracked up to be.

43
00:03:01,311 --> 00:03:02,604
Depends on the therapist.

44
00:03:02,687 --> 00:03:05,315
SAM: <i>They'll move
on the building soon. Be ready.</i>

45
00:03:05,398 --> 00:03:06,983
(WHOOSHING)

46
00:03:12,155 --> 00:03:14,366
He's here. Do it now.

47
00:03:21,915 --> 00:03:23,291
(HISSING)

48
00:03:23,375 --> 00:03:25,960
(ALL CLAMORING)

49
00:03:28,588 --> 00:03:30,965
MAN: Keep your head down.
Move toward the door, sir.

50
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:32,717
(COUGHING)

51
00:03:32,801 --> 00:03:36,012
(ALL COUGHING AND SCREAMING)

52
00:03:39,682 --> 00:03:41,142
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

53
00:03:41,226 --> 00:03:42,477
(WINGS WHOOSHING)

54
00:03:44,145 --> 00:03:45,814
(MAN GROANS)

55
00:03:56,241 --> 00:03:58,451
Sharon, Bucky,
what's going on on your end?

56
00:03:58,535 --> 00:04:00,036
Nothing. All quiet.

57
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:01,663
I'm sorry, wait. Who are you?

58
00:04:01,746 --> 00:04:04,124
- I'm Captain America.
- I thought he was on the Moon.

59
00:04:04,749 --> 00:04:06,626
No one's moving toward the building.

60
00:04:06,709 --> 00:04:09,629
Karli's not coming in.
She's trying to force everybody out.

61
00:04:09,712 --> 00:04:12,090
- East evac teams...
- CAPTAIN AMERICA: It's a misdirect.

62
00:04:12,173 --> 00:04:13,425
We gotta keep everybody inside.

63
00:04:13,508 --> 00:04:14,551
(BOTH GRUNTING)

64
00:04:16,928 --> 00:04:19,848
You cost me a lot of money.

65
00:04:19,931 --> 00:04:22,934
I wonder how much I can get
for your new bird costume.

66
00:04:23,017 --> 00:04:24,561
A baguette and a few French fries.

67
00:04:24,644 --> 00:04:25,812
(IN FRENCH)
The robes don't make the monk.

68
00:04:27,605 --> 00:04:28,898
(CAPTAIN AMERICA GRUNTS)

69
00:04:29,899 --> 00:04:31,568
You guys are gonna have to do something.

70
00:04:31,651 --> 00:04:33,611
(OVER RADIO)
<i>Don't let 'em out of the building.</i>

71
00:04:33,695 --> 00:04:35,822
- (ALARM BEEPS)
- Oops.

72
00:04:36,698 --> 00:04:37,699
Here's one of them.

73
00:04:38,950 --> 00:04:40,034
I'll get the evac.

74
00:04:40,952 --> 00:04:43,413
Lennox, they're heading down
the east stairwell.

75
00:04:44,122 --> 00:04:46,249
ANNOUNCER: (OVER SPEAKER)
<i>This is an emergency evacuation.</i>

76
00:04:46,332 --> 00:04:48,376
<i>Please proceed to your transports.</i>

77
00:04:48,460 --> 00:04:51,629
<i>Groups one and two will leave
from secure vehicles in the basement.</i>

78
00:04:51,713 --> 00:04:54,007
<i>Group three will leave
via air support on the roof</i>

79
00:04:54,090 --> 00:04:55,258
( INDISTINCT CHATTER)

80
00:05:06,853 --> 00:05:09,522
Mr. Barnes, it's Karli.

81
00:05:15,028 --> 00:05:16,029
(OVER CELL PHONE) <i>Karli?</i>

82
00:05:16,112 --> 00:05:18,615
KARLI: Aren't you tired
of fighting for the wrong side?

83
00:05:18,698 --> 00:05:20,742
(SCOFFS) I've done this before, kid.

84
00:05:20,825 --> 00:05:21,993
I know how it ends.

85
00:05:22,076 --> 00:05:24,871
It doesn't matter if I don't survive this.

86
00:05:24,954 --> 00:05:26,915
I'm fighting for something
bigger than myself.

87
00:05:26,998 --> 00:05:30,043
With all the bodies you've collected,
have you been able to say the same?

88
00:05:30,126 --> 00:05:33,171
You don't think I ever fought
for something bigger than myself?

89
00:05:33,254 --> 00:05:36,090
That's all I ever tried to do.
And I failed twice.

90
00:05:36,174 --> 00:05:37,675
(SIREN WAILING)

91
00:05:44,307 --> 00:05:45,517
( INDISTINCT CHATTER)

92
00:06:08,623 --> 00:06:09,624
(BEEPS)

93
00:06:24,097 --> 00:06:25,390
(BEEPS)

94
00:06:26,432 --> 00:06:27,850
(BOTH GRUNTING)

95
00:06:30,562 --> 00:06:31,729
(CAPTAIN AMERICA GROANS)

96
00:06:36,734 --> 00:06:38,778
You think your cause
justifies all this death,

97
00:06:38,861 --> 00:06:40,697
but in the end,
the nightmares won't go away.

98
00:06:40,780 --> 00:06:43,825
<i>You're gonna remember
all the ones you killed.</i>

99
00:06:43,908 --> 00:06:44,909
Trust me.

100
00:06:45,952 --> 00:06:46,953
Don't do this.

101
00:06:47,787 --> 00:06:49,080
Don't go down this path.

102
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:54,419
If that's how you feel,
you should sit this one out.

103
00:06:55,044 --> 00:06:56,838
Come on, you know I ain't gonna do that.

104
00:06:57,672 --> 00:06:58,673
Well, thank you.

105
00:06:58,756 --> 00:07:01,342
<i>I'm glad you took my call.
You've been a big help.</i>

106
00:07:03,469 --> 00:07:04,637
Damn it!

107
00:07:12,228 --> 00:07:15,023
LENNOX: Hostages en route.
ETA, six minutes.

108
00:07:17,358 --> 00:07:19,485
Seriously, Bucky, you had one job.

109
00:07:19,569 --> 00:07:21,779
- You worry about your guy.
- (ENGINE WHIRRING)

110
00:07:26,826 --> 00:07:28,703
(TIRES SCREECH)

111
00:07:28,786 --> 00:07:29,954
Oh, my... I'm so sorry.

112
00:07:30,038 --> 00:07:31,706
I didn't see you, I'm sorry.

113
00:07:42,175 --> 00:07:43,176
SOLDIER: Hey!

114
00:07:44,844 --> 00:07:45,928
(ENGINE ACCELERATING)

115
00:07:50,975 --> 00:07:53,227
- (MUFFLED EXPLOSION)
- (TIRES SCREECH)

116
00:07:53,936 --> 00:07:55,271
(HISSING)

117
00:07:57,732 --> 00:07:59,942
- Well, that's one down.
- How'd you manage that?

118
00:08:00,026 --> 00:08:01,152
(GRUNTS)

119
00:08:01,903 --> 00:08:03,946
Mercury vapor, amongst other things.

120
00:08:14,332 --> 00:08:15,583
Boarding now.

121
00:08:19,587 --> 00:08:22,131
- You better speed things up.
- (HELICOPTER HOVERING)

122
00:08:22,215 --> 00:08:23,508
The chopper's about to take off.

123
00:08:24,175 --> 00:08:25,885
- (GRUNTS)
- Bucky!

124
00:08:25,968 --> 00:08:27,637
(BOTH GRUNTING)

125
00:08:28,846 --> 00:08:31,140
- I don't fly, man. That's your thing.
- (ENGINE REVS)

126
00:08:34,602 --> 00:08:35,895
(GRUNTS)

127
00:08:35,978 --> 00:08:37,647
(CLANKING)

128
00:08:39,941 --> 00:08:41,484
(BOTH GRUNTING)

129
00:08:48,741 --> 00:08:49,826
- (CLANKING)
- (GRUNTS)

130
00:08:52,912 --> 00:08:53,913
(GEORGES GRUNTS)

131
00:08:55,206 --> 00:08:56,207
(IN FRENCH) <i>Au revoir!</i>

132
00:08:57,625 --> 00:08:58,793
(GLASS SHATTERS)

133
00:09:00,211 --> 00:09:01,671
- (GRUNTS)
- (WINGS WHOOSHING)

134
00:09:05,341 --> 00:09:07,802
Moving to the rendezvous,
about eight to ten minutes out.

135
00:09:16,018 --> 00:09:17,270
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

136
00:09:19,021 --> 00:09:20,523
(WINGS WHOOSHING)

137
00:09:22,442 --> 00:09:23,735
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

138
00:09:44,088 --> 00:09:45,089
(CAPTAIN AMERICA GRUNTS)

139
00:09:48,968 --> 00:09:51,679
Redwing, see if anyone in there
has flight training.

140
00:09:57,226 --> 00:09:58,770
(BEEPING)

141
00:10:00,438 --> 00:10:01,814
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

142
00:10:07,111 --> 00:10:08,780
DOVICH: Boss, Lennox ain't responding.

143
00:10:08,863 --> 00:10:10,782
DEEDEE: We can still
get out of here before...

144
00:10:10,865 --> 00:10:13,618
No. Diego's in the air.
The trucks are almost here.

145
00:10:13,701 --> 00:10:17,079
Worst case scenario... we kill the hostages.

146
00:10:18,372 --> 00:10:21,542
- We're supposed to use them to negotiate.
- To stop that vote.

147
00:10:24,086 --> 00:10:25,963
Either way,
our message gets out to the world.

148
00:10:28,090 --> 00:10:29,801
It doesn't even matter if we die.

149
00:10:29,884 --> 00:10:32,345
The movement is strong enough
to continue without us.

150
00:10:38,518 --> 00:10:40,770
Hope for the best. Prepare for the worst.

151
00:10:40,853 --> 00:10:42,396
Hold tight. Move fast.

152
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:43,481
One world.

153
00:10:48,361 --> 00:10:49,487
One world.

154
00:10:49,570 --> 00:10:50,822
One people.

155
00:10:50,905 --> 00:10:51,948
One people.

156
00:10:52,031 --> 00:10:53,282
One people.

157
00:10:54,325 --> 00:10:55,952
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

158
00:11:01,666 --> 00:11:02,917
(ENGINE ACCELERATING)

159
00:11:18,307 --> 00:11:19,433
(BLASTS)

160
00:11:19,517 --> 00:11:20,852
(BEEPING)

161
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:23,521
(PILOT 1 SCREAMS)

162
00:11:24,146 --> 00:11:25,481
(PILOT 2 SCREAMS)

163
00:11:26,315 --> 00:11:27,316
(PILOT 2 SCREAMS)

164
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,484
(PILOT 2 GRUNTS)

165
00:11:29,694 --> 00:11:30,778
- (HELICOPTER WHIRRING)
- (CLANKS)

166
00:11:32,947 --> 00:11:33,948
(THUDS)

167
00:11:35,199 --> 00:11:36,576
MAN: Yeah, man!

168
00:11:36,659 --> 00:11:37,994
(CROWD CHEERING)

169
00:11:39,161 --> 00:11:40,162
MAN: Whoo!

170
00:11:47,211 --> 00:11:48,462
( INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER RADIO)

171
00:11:49,380 --> 00:11:51,257
(TIRES SCREECHING)

172
00:11:53,134 --> 00:11:55,136
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

173
00:11:59,390 --> 00:12:00,641
(ALL CLAMORING)

174
00:12:02,393 --> 00:12:04,770
(DRIVER GRUNTS)

175
00:12:05,521 --> 00:12:06,772
(SCREAMS AND GROANS)

176
00:12:11,319 --> 00:12:12,695
(ENGINE ACCELERATING)

177
00:12:21,954 --> 00:12:24,707
(BOTH GRUNTING)

178
00:12:28,461 --> 00:12:30,004
(KARLI GRUNTS)

179
00:12:32,089 --> 00:12:34,467
KARLI: We need a diversion.
Give him someone to rescue.

180
00:12:34,550 --> 00:12:36,510
- GIGI: What do you mean?
- KARLI: Light it up.

181
00:12:39,013 --> 00:12:41,182
- MAN: Help! Help us! Help!
- WOMAN: Get over here!

182
00:12:44,518 --> 00:12:45,603
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

183
00:12:47,939 --> 00:12:49,815
(BOTH GRUNTING)

184
00:12:52,401 --> 00:12:54,528
(ALL SCREAMING)

185
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:57,281
Hold on!

186
00:12:59,742 --> 00:13:00,826
DOVICH: Let's go, get moving!

187
00:13:01,327 --> 00:13:02,912
WALKER: Morgenthau!

188
00:13:08,334 --> 00:13:09,418
Let's finish this.

189
00:13:09,502 --> 00:13:11,504
I didn't mean to kill your friend.

190
00:13:11,587 --> 00:13:13,464
I don't wanna hurt people
that don't matter.

191
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,885
You don't think Lemar's life mattered?

192
00:13:18,511 --> 00:13:19,929
KARLI: Not to my fight.

193
00:13:20,012 --> 00:13:21,931
I just want the people on that truck.

194
00:13:22,014 --> 00:13:23,307
(SCREAMS)

195
00:13:23,391 --> 00:13:24,642
- (GRUNTS)
- (CLANKS)

196
00:13:33,234 --> 00:13:34,276
(GRUNTS)

197
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:35,611
We gotta get out of here.

198
00:13:36,278 --> 00:13:38,197
(GRUNTING)

199
00:13:48,874 --> 00:13:49,917
(GRUNTS)

200
00:13:53,546 --> 00:13:55,047
(BOTH GRUNTING)

201
00:13:57,675 --> 00:14:00,261
(ALL GRUNTING)

202
00:14:08,352 --> 00:14:09,854
MAN: Be careful. I've got you.

203
00:14:09,937 --> 00:14:11,355
BUCKY: Go. Go!

204
00:14:11,439 --> 00:14:13,065
MAN: Thank you for saving us.

205
00:14:14,608 --> 00:14:15,609
You're welcome.

206
00:14:16,610 --> 00:14:19,196
(DOVICH GRUNTING)

207
00:14:21,615 --> 00:14:22,908
(SCREAMS)

208
00:14:34,086 --> 00:14:36,047
(KARLI GRUNTING)

209
00:14:38,549 --> 00:14:40,384
- (KARLI GRUNTS)
- (DOVICH SCREAMS)

210
00:14:40,468 --> 00:14:42,887
(GRUNTS AND SCREAMS)

211
00:14:46,390 --> 00:14:47,808
(GRUNTS)

212
00:14:55,524 --> 00:14:56,942
- (GUN FIRING)
- (ALL SCREAMING)

213
00:15:01,197 --> 00:15:02,573
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

214
00:15:06,535 --> 00:15:09,955
CAPTAIN AMERICA: <i>A little birdie told me
you know how to fly a helicopter.</i>

215
00:15:12,208 --> 00:15:15,211
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa! (SCREAMS)

216
00:15:15,294 --> 00:15:16,796
(GRUNTS)

217
00:15:18,547 --> 00:15:19,757
(GROANS)

218
00:15:32,186 --> 00:15:33,395
Whoa!

219
00:15:33,479 --> 00:15:35,981
Boy, you just earned this ass-whoopin'.

220
00:15:38,275 --> 00:15:40,861
Okay. What we're gonna do
requires perfect timing.

221
00:15:40,945 --> 00:15:42,655
<i>We're gonna count down from five.</i>

222
00:15:42,738 --> 00:15:45,658
When we get to one,
you're gonna grab the control.

223
00:15:45,741 --> 00:15:46,867
<i>Okay?</i>

224
00:15:49,745 --> 00:15:50,996
Five...

225
00:15:51,872 --> 00:15:53,040
Four...

226
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:54,834
Three...

227
00:15:55,918 --> 00:15:57,336
Two...

228
00:15:59,171 --> 00:16:00,172
(GRUNTS)

229
00:16:03,134 --> 00:16:04,802
(BEEPING)

230
00:16:07,847 --> 00:16:10,182
(ALL SCREAMING)

231
00:16:13,394 --> 00:16:14,562
(GRUNTS)

232
00:16:15,146 --> 00:16:16,188
(SCREAMS)

233
00:16:21,944 --> 00:16:23,112
Nice work, Ayla.

234
00:16:24,697 --> 00:16:26,282
(PANTING)

235
00:16:30,077 --> 00:16:31,412
(GRUNTS)

236
00:16:31,495 --> 00:16:32,788
(BOTH GRUNTING)

237
00:16:33,706 --> 00:16:36,292
- (CLANKS)
- (WOMAN GROANING)

238
00:16:36,375 --> 00:16:38,502
(GRUNTS)

239
00:16:41,714 --> 00:16:43,883
- WOMAN: Help! Help!
- MAN: Somebody help!

240
00:16:45,384 --> 00:16:46,927
(GRUNTS)

241
00:16:50,306 --> 00:16:51,682
(BOTH GRUNTING)

242
00:17:02,443 --> 00:17:03,903
- (CLANKS)
- (GRUNTS)

243
00:17:09,158 --> 00:17:10,576
(KARLI GROANS)

244
00:17:13,329 --> 00:17:14,330
(KARLI GRUNTS)

245
00:17:25,674 --> 00:17:26,800
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

246
00:17:36,060 --> 00:17:37,061
(GRUNTS)

247
00:17:41,273 --> 00:17:42,441
(KARLI GRUNTS)

248
00:17:44,818 --> 00:17:46,403
(ALL SCREAMING)

249
00:17:48,364 --> 00:17:49,657
(CREAKING)

250
00:17:56,455 --> 00:17:58,540
(CREAKING AND CLANKING)

251
00:17:58,624 --> 00:18:01,460
(PANTING)

252
00:18:02,253 --> 00:18:03,462
(THUDS)

253
00:18:07,132 --> 00:18:09,260
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

254
00:18:13,055 --> 00:18:14,098
(CREAKING)

255
00:18:21,689 --> 00:18:23,399
(GRUNTING)

256
00:18:29,905 --> 00:18:31,073
(GRUNTING)

257
00:18:32,366 --> 00:18:34,326
(ALL GRUNTING)

258
00:18:34,410 --> 00:18:36,161
(ALL SCREAMING)

259
00:18:36,245 --> 00:18:37,746
(ALL GROANING)

260
00:18:37,830 --> 00:18:39,039
(CREAKING)

261
00:18:39,123 --> 00:18:40,582
- WOMAN: No!
- (ALL SCREAMING)

262
00:18:46,505 --> 00:18:48,048
(CREAKING)

263
00:18:49,466 --> 00:18:51,093
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

264
00:19:04,106 --> 00:19:05,024
(GRUNTS)

265
00:19:11,905 --> 00:19:13,073
(GRUNTING)

266
00:19:22,166 --> 00:19:23,751
- (ALL CHEERING)
- Hell, yeah!

267
00:19:25,419 --> 00:19:28,797
That's the Black Falcon there. I tell you.

268
00:19:29,423 --> 00:19:31,675
Nah, that's Captain America.

269
00:19:41,018 --> 00:19:42,186
(KARLI GRUNTS)

270
00:19:44,772 --> 00:19:47,941
(CLANKING)

271
00:19:52,780 --> 00:19:54,656
You of all people
bought into that bullshit?

272
00:19:54,740 --> 00:19:57,701
I'm trying something different.
Maybe you should do the same.

273
00:19:58,869 --> 00:19:59,745
(EXPLOSION)

274
00:20:02,790 --> 00:20:04,833
(GUN FIRING)

275
00:20:06,418 --> 00:20:07,795
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

276
00:20:23,644 --> 00:20:24,728
This way.

277
00:20:40,869 --> 00:20:42,621
BUCKY: Hey, Sharon. We're underground.

278
00:20:42,704 --> 00:20:45,124
We entered the tunnel on William.
Heading south.

279
00:20:48,419 --> 00:20:50,504
Looks like they split up. Here.

280
00:20:52,381 --> 00:20:53,382
I got it.

281
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:12,484
(WHISTLING)

282
00:21:24,955 --> 00:21:26,915
(WHISTLING)

283
00:21:37,217 --> 00:21:38,802
(WHISTLING)

284
00:21:38,886 --> 00:21:40,012
Dovich?

285
00:21:40,888 --> 00:21:42,598
Dovich, is that you?

286
00:21:44,349 --> 00:21:45,851
Drop your weapon, Karli.

287
00:21:48,937 --> 00:21:49,980
I said drop it.

288
00:21:53,734 --> 00:21:54,943
I'm disappointed in you.

289
00:21:57,029 --> 00:21:58,238
That's what I was gonna say.

290
00:22:08,165 --> 00:22:11,251
You know, when you came to Madripoor,
you reminded me of a young me.

291
00:22:12,127 --> 00:22:14,963
I took you in, gave you an opportunity,

292
00:22:16,423 --> 00:22:17,424
and you betrayed me.

293
00:22:17,508 --> 00:22:19,635
Because you wanted
to control a world that hurt you.

294
00:22:19,718 --> 00:22:21,053
But I wanted to change it.

295
00:22:21,887 --> 00:22:23,972
I'm not interested in power or an empire.

296
00:22:24,806 --> 00:22:26,558
- I have bigger dreams.
- SHARON: What, like this?

297
00:22:26,642 --> 00:22:28,852
Come back and work for me again.
All of you.

298
00:22:28,936 --> 00:22:30,604
We can make a difference together.

299
00:22:31,355 --> 00:22:33,607
You just want me
because you need your muscle back.

300
00:22:34,107 --> 00:22:37,653
Without us Super Soldiers, how much power
does the Power Broker really have?

301
00:22:39,613 --> 00:22:41,031
More than you.

302
00:22:44,576 --> 00:22:46,161
So, you're the Power Broker.

303
00:22:50,040 --> 00:22:51,542
You hired Batroc to spy on me.

304
00:22:52,084 --> 00:22:53,835
Karli, you know I'm always prepared.

305
00:22:53,919 --> 00:22:55,212
Get outta my way.

306
00:22:56,004 --> 00:22:57,589
I'm done with these games.

307
00:23:00,008 --> 00:23:01,718
(IN FRENCH)
Now Power Broker...

308
00:23:02,844 --> 00:23:03,679
you will pay me...

309
00:23:04,096 --> 00:23:06,139
four times what you said you would.

310
00:23:06,223 --> 00:23:07,891
(IN ENGLISH) Four times. Or...

311
00:23:08,559 --> 00:23:10,811
(IN FRENCH)
I'll tell the whole world who you are.

312
00:23:10,894 --> 00:23:11,895
(IN ENGLISH) Okay?

313
00:23:14,690 --> 00:23:15,857
I don't do blackmail.

314
00:23:21,196 --> 00:23:23,323
(GASPING)

315
00:23:30,539 --> 00:23:31,873
Sam, stay back.

316
00:23:32,666 --> 00:23:33,667
So, what's next, huh?

317
00:23:34,209 --> 00:23:36,461
You kill ten this time,
then, what, a hundred?

318
00:23:37,045 --> 00:23:38,171
Where does it end?

319
00:23:39,006 --> 00:23:41,049
Please, let me help you.

320
00:23:42,009 --> 00:23:43,427
Don't try and manipulate me.

321
00:23:45,012 --> 00:23:46,054
Karli, don't!

322
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:51,393
(BOTH GRUNTING)

323
00:23:54,146 --> 00:23:56,106
I'm not gonna fight you!

324
00:24:00,444 --> 00:24:01,903
Karli...

325
00:24:09,202 --> 00:24:10,537
Stay down!

326
00:24:12,873 --> 00:24:13,874
No.

327
00:24:17,961 --> 00:24:20,047
The app says it's this way.

328
00:24:21,214 --> 00:24:22,215
Let's go.

329
00:24:26,887 --> 00:24:30,474
"Mercy bears
richer fruit than strict justice."

330
00:24:31,808 --> 00:24:33,310
It's a great app.

331
00:24:34,853 --> 00:24:35,854
( INDISTINCT CHATTER)

332
00:24:37,731 --> 00:24:38,899
Thank you.

333
00:24:47,866 --> 00:24:49,201
BUCKY: Lincoln, really?

334
00:24:49,284 --> 00:24:50,869
Great man. Great quote.

335
00:24:50,952 --> 00:24:52,371
Not when you say it.

336
00:24:52,913 --> 00:24:54,373
(BOTH GRUNTING)

337
00:24:54,456 --> 00:24:55,707
Fight back!

338
00:25:03,423 --> 00:25:05,092
Stop it!

339
00:25:08,178 --> 00:25:10,764
Fight me! Fight back!

340
00:25:35,997 --> 00:25:37,082
(GUN FIRING)

341
00:25:41,962 --> 00:25:42,963
(EXHALES)

342
00:25:54,933 --> 00:25:56,059
KARLI: (WHISPERING) I'm sorry.

343
00:26:05,277 --> 00:26:06,278
(SOBBING)

344
00:26:23,962 --> 00:26:25,213
(SIGHS IN RELIEF)

345
00:27:10,217 --> 00:27:11,635
( INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER RADIO)

346
00:27:20,602 --> 00:27:22,646
REPORTER 1: What happened
to the Flag Smashers?

347
00:27:22,729 --> 00:27:24,815
When did the government
make you Captain America?

348
00:27:24,898 --> 00:27:27,776
- REPORTER 1: Is it still Falcon?
- REPORTER 2: Or is it Captain Falcon?

349
00:27:27,859 --> 00:27:30,737
AYLA: Sam, thank you so much,
from all of us.

350
00:27:31,446 --> 00:27:32,781
SENATOR: Sincerely.

351
00:27:32,864 --> 00:27:36,159
You did your part in dealing
with those terrorists, now we'll do ours.

352
00:27:36,743 --> 00:27:39,329
Are you still going forward
with resetting the borders?

353
00:27:39,412 --> 00:27:42,165
Our peacekeeping troops
will begin relocating people soon.

354
00:27:42,249 --> 00:27:44,459
The terrorists only set us back a bit.

355
00:27:44,543 --> 00:27:46,211
Stop calling them terrorists.

356
00:27:46,294 --> 00:27:48,171
What else would we call them?

357
00:27:48,255 --> 00:27:50,590
Your peacekeeping troops carrying weapons

358
00:27:50,674 --> 00:27:54,135
are forcing millions of people
into settlements around the world, right?

359
00:27:54,219 --> 00:27:56,680
What do you think
those people are gonna call you?

360
00:27:58,557 --> 00:28:02,644
These labels,
"terrorists," "refugee," "thug,"

361
00:28:02,727 --> 00:28:05,647
they're often used
to get around the question, why?

362
00:28:05,730 --> 00:28:08,483
LACONT: Those settlements
that happened five years ago,

363
00:28:09,276 --> 00:28:13,405
do you think it is fair for governments
to have to support them?

364
00:28:13,488 --> 00:28:14,489
Yes.

365
00:28:14,573 --> 00:28:16,658
SENATOR: And the people who reappeared

366
00:28:16,741 --> 00:28:19,160
only to find someone else
living in their family home,

367
00:28:19,244 --> 00:28:20,412
they just end up homeless?

368
00:28:21,663 --> 00:28:22,956
Look, I get it.

369
00:28:23,039 --> 00:28:27,502
But you have no idea
how complicated this situation is.

370
00:28:29,296 --> 00:28:30,672
You know what? You're right.

371
00:28:32,048 --> 00:28:33,133
And that's a good thing.

372
00:28:35,218 --> 00:28:38,513
We finally have a common struggle now.

373
00:28:38,597 --> 00:28:39,639
Think about that.

374
00:28:40,640 --> 00:28:43,268
For once,
all the people who've been begging,

375
00:28:43,351 --> 00:28:46,021
and I mean, literally begging for you

376
00:28:46,104 --> 00:28:48,648
to feel how hard any given day is...

377
00:28:49,232 --> 00:28:50,400
Now you know.

378
00:28:50,483 --> 00:28:52,736
How did it feel to be helpless?

379
00:28:54,237 --> 00:28:57,073
Now if you could remember
what it was like to be helpless

380
00:28:57,699 --> 00:29:00,994
and face a force so powerful
it could erase half the planet,

381
00:29:02,370 --> 00:29:05,749
you would know that you're about
to have the exact same impact.

382
00:29:07,459 --> 00:29:10,462
This isn't about easy decisions, Senator.

383
00:29:10,545 --> 00:29:11,588
You don't understand.

384
00:29:11,671 --> 00:29:15,675
(SCOFFS) I'm a Black man
carrying the stars and stripes.

385
00:29:16,217 --> 00:29:18,011
What don't I understand?

386
00:29:20,013 --> 00:29:21,723
Every time I pick this thing up,

387
00:29:22,599 --> 00:29:25,602
I know there are millions of people
who are gonna hate me for it.

388
00:29:28,063 --> 00:29:30,065
Even now, here...

389
00:29:30,774 --> 00:29:31,775
<i>I feel it.</i>

390
00:29:32,859 --> 00:29:34,235
<i>The stares, the judgment.</i>

391
00:29:35,111 --> 00:29:37,155
<i>And there's nothin' I can do to change it.</i>

392
00:29:39,282 --> 00:29:40,450
<i>Yet,</i> l'<i>m still here.</i>

393
00:29:41,910 --> 00:29:45,830
<i>No super serum,
no blond hair, or blue eyes.</i>

394
00:29:48,833 --> 00:29:55,048
The only power I have
is that I believe we can do better.

395
00:29:56,967 --> 00:30:00,929
We can't demand that people step up
if we don't meet them halfway.

396
00:30:01,012 --> 00:30:02,931
Look, you control the banks.

397
00:30:03,014 --> 00:30:07,143
Shit, you can move borders!
You can knock down a forest with an email,

398
00:30:07,227 --> 00:30:10,522
<i>you can feed a million people
with a phone call.</i>

399
00:30:11,189 --> 00:30:12,190
<i>But the question is,</i>

400
00:30:13,358 --> 00:30:15,485
<i>who's in the room
when you make those decisions?</i>

401
00:30:15,568 --> 00:30:17,028
<i>Hmm?</i>

402
00:30:17,112 --> 00:30:18,905
<i>Is it the people you're gonna impact?</i>

403
00:30:19,572 --> 00:30:21,241
Or is it just more people like you?

404
00:30:26,037 --> 00:30:29,541
I mean, this girl died trying to stop you,

405
00:30:30,125 --> 00:30:33,420
and no one has stopped
for one second to ask why.

406
00:30:33,503 --> 00:30:35,588
You've gotta do better, Senator.

407
00:30:35,672 --> 00:30:37,090
You've gotta step up.

408
00:30:37,674 --> 00:30:39,592
Because if you don't, the next Karli will.

409
00:30:40,385 --> 00:30:42,178
And you don't wanna see 2.0.

410
00:30:43,096 --> 00:30:45,890
People believed in her cause so much

411
00:30:47,017 --> 00:30:51,438
that they helped her defy
the strongest governments in the world.

412
00:30:52,856 --> 00:30:54,399
Why do you think that is?

413
00:30:56,568 --> 00:31:00,613
Look, you people have just as much power
as an insane god

414
00:31:02,323 --> 00:31:03,867
or a misguided teenager.

415
00:31:05,618 --> 00:31:07,620
The question you have to ask yourself is,

416
00:31:08,538 --> 00:31:10,415
"How are you going to use it?"

417
00:31:26,514 --> 00:31:28,850
Sorry, I was, uh, I was texting and so,

418
00:31:28,933 --> 00:31:31,436
all I heard was, um,
"a Black guy in stars and stripes."

419
00:31:31,519 --> 00:31:32,604
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

420
00:31:33,688 --> 00:31:35,023
Nice job, Cap.

421
00:31:35,106 --> 00:31:36,107
Thanks.

422
00:31:39,194 --> 00:31:40,737
SAM: Sharon?

423
00:31:42,655 --> 00:31:43,698
Blocking my light.

424
00:31:45,116 --> 00:31:46,493
SAM: We gotta get you to a hospital.

425
00:31:46,576 --> 00:31:47,786
She's not gonna listen.

426
00:31:47,869 --> 00:31:50,705
(PANTING) It's not the worst thing
that's happened to me all week.

427
00:31:50,789 --> 00:31:52,082
Told you.

428
00:31:52,165 --> 00:31:53,249
MAN: Uh, Cap?

429
00:31:54,334 --> 00:31:56,044
(BREATHING HEAVILY) I think
he's talking to you.

430
00:31:57,545 --> 00:31:59,923
Look, I'm sorry
for how things ended down there.

431
00:32:02,300 --> 00:32:05,011
For what it's worth,
suit looks good on you.

432
00:32:05,678 --> 00:32:07,222
(CHUCKLES) Thanks.

433
00:32:07,305 --> 00:32:09,557
All right, look,
can we get out of here, please?

434
00:32:09,641 --> 00:32:11,267
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

435
00:32:12,477 --> 00:32:13,561
I didn't forget my promise.

436
00:32:17,315 --> 00:32:18,733
What's up?

437
00:32:18,817 --> 00:32:21,778
So, we got eyes on the last
Flag Smasher that fell into the Hudson.

438
00:32:21,861 --> 00:32:23,947
He's hurt but not down. Can you help?

439
00:32:24,489 --> 00:32:25,907
Always.

440
00:32:27,492 --> 00:32:29,285
(THRILLING INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

441
00:32:37,001 --> 00:32:39,295
( INDISTINCT CHATTER)

442
00:32:42,090 --> 00:32:44,509
OFFICER: <i>Confirming that prisoners
have cleared final processing.</i>

443
00:32:44,592 --> 00:32:46,427
<i>We are transporting them to the Raft.</i>

444
00:32:56,771 --> 00:32:58,398
One world. One people.

445
00:33:13,329 --> 00:33:17,041
- ( INDISTINCT SHOUTING)
- (SIRENS APPROACHING)

446
00:33:24,382 --> 00:33:26,634
REPORTER: <i>Four members
of the radical group, the Flag Smashers,</i>

447
00:33:26,718 --> 00:33:28,386
<i>were killed today in a car bomb attack</i>

448
00:33:28,469 --> 00:33:31,514
<i>as they were being transferred
to a high-security prison.</i>

449
00:33:31,598 --> 00:33:33,516
<i>There are no suspects in the bombing.</i>

450
00:33:33,600 --> 00:33:36,895
<i>The group had opposed
the global relocation efforts of the GRC,</i>

451
00:33:36,978 --> 00:33:38,771
who, <i>just this week, had announced changes</i>

452
00:33:38,855 --> 00:33:42,650
<i>in their overall policies
of repatriation and resettlement.</i>

453
00:33:43,651 --> 00:33:44,652
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

454
00:33:45,904 --> 00:33:46,905
VALENTINA: Oh!

455
00:33:47,864 --> 00:33:50,700
Ooh. Hey, Walker, check your phone.

456
00:33:51,409 --> 00:33:57,081
Looks like our friend, Zemo,
kinda got the last laugh, right?

457
00:33:57,916 --> 00:33:58,917
Wow.

458
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:01,502
Couldn't have worked better
if I planned it myself.

459
00:34:02,295 --> 00:34:05,673
Oh. Well, maybe I did.
No, I'm kidding, I didn't.

460
00:34:07,050 --> 00:34:08,718
Or did I?

461
00:34:10,428 --> 00:34:12,972
Anyway, it's gonna save people
a lot of paperwork

462
00:34:13,056 --> 00:34:15,350
and a lot of redacting
and a lot of shredding.

463
00:34:17,101 --> 00:34:18,102
(EXHALES, CLEARS THROAT)

464
00:34:21,522 --> 00:34:25,068
What is he doing in there?

465
00:34:25,151 --> 00:34:26,945
It's probably the helmet.

466
00:34:27,779 --> 00:34:30,657
Walker! My God! Let's go!

467
00:34:31,991 --> 00:34:32,992
(DOOR OPENS)

468
00:34:38,790 --> 00:34:41,000
VALENTINA: Now, this is more like it.

469
00:34:42,460 --> 00:34:45,213
It's the same, but black.

470
00:34:46,047 --> 00:34:47,924
- Yeah, well...
- Yeah.

471
00:34:48,007 --> 00:34:50,093
VALENTINA: Things are about to get weird.

472
00:34:50,760 --> 00:34:55,640
So, when they do,
we're not gonna need a Captain America.

473
00:34:57,475 --> 00:35:01,312
We're gonna need a U.S. Agent.

474
00:35:03,147 --> 00:35:05,441
- WALKER: That's great.
- Keep your phone on.

475
00:35:06,359 --> 00:35:08,444
- Will do, Val.
- Don't call me that.

476
00:35:08,528 --> 00:35:09,946
Copy.

477
00:35:10,029 --> 00:35:11,197
Thank you.

478
00:35:13,157 --> 00:35:15,076
MRS. WALKER: U.S. Agent. (LAUGHS)

479
00:35:17,996 --> 00:35:21,624
- I'm back! I'm back! I'm back! I'm back!
- (CHUCKLING)

480
00:35:38,975 --> 00:35:39,976
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

481
00:35:44,147 --> 00:35:46,357
Hey, what are you doing here?

482
00:35:47,358 --> 00:35:49,861
It's late,
come in before someone call the cops.

483
00:35:55,742 --> 00:35:57,952
What are you doing here?
It's not Wednesday.

484
00:36:00,788 --> 00:36:03,583
I, uh, I have to tell you something.

485
00:36:05,585 --> 00:36:06,627
About your son.

486
00:36:15,094 --> 00:36:16,346
He was murdered.

487
00:36:17,597 --> 00:36:19,390
What?

488
00:36:20,308 --> 00:36:21,893
By the Winter Soldier.

489
00:36:25,688 --> 00:36:26,856
(VOICE SHAKING) And that was me.

490
00:36:30,109 --> 00:36:31,152
Why?

491
00:36:31,778 --> 00:36:32,862
( INHALES)

492
00:36:34,989 --> 00:36:36,366
I didn't have a choice.

493
00:38:03,703 --> 00:38:04,704
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

494
00:38:11,461 --> 00:38:12,753
What you want, Black Falcon?

495
00:38:12,837 --> 00:38:14,630
Hey, you need to learn some manners.

496
00:38:15,882 --> 00:38:17,633
ISAIAH: He ain't a Falcon anymore,

497
00:38:19,093 --> 00:38:20,219
but he's still Black.

498
00:38:27,268 --> 00:38:28,811
I saw what you did out there.

499
00:38:32,023 --> 00:38:34,192
And it seems, so did everyone else.

500
00:38:35,401 --> 00:38:38,988
I heard the GRC was standing down
on those plans of theirs,

501
00:38:39,071 --> 00:38:41,199
so you must have done somethin' right.

502
00:38:46,829 --> 00:38:47,914
I ain't gonna lie.

503
00:38:48,915 --> 00:38:49,916
You're special.

504
00:38:52,543 --> 00:38:53,586
Thank you.

505
00:38:55,171 --> 00:38:59,634
I mean, you ain't no Malcolm,
Martin, Mandela, but...

506
00:38:59,717 --> 00:39:00,801
No argument there.

507
00:39:01,469 --> 00:39:03,054
But I know what I've gotta do.

508
00:39:05,515 --> 00:39:08,518
So, a Black Captain America, huh?

509
00:39:09,393 --> 00:39:10,770
Damn right.

510
00:39:12,605 --> 00:39:14,023
(CHUCKLES)

511
00:39:14,106 --> 00:39:17,318
The fight you taking on
ain't gonna be easy, Sam.

512
00:39:18,861 --> 00:39:19,946
SAM: Yeah, I might fail.

513
00:39:20,988 --> 00:39:22,823
Shit, I might die.

514
00:39:23,741 --> 00:39:24,825
But...

515
00:39:25,493 --> 00:39:26,619
We built this country.

516
00:39:27,453 --> 00:39:28,538
Bled for it.

517
00:39:30,081 --> 00:39:32,750
I'm not gonna let
anybody tell me I can't fight for it.

518
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:36,546
Not after what everybody
before me went through.

519
00:39:36,629 --> 00:39:37,922
Including you.

520
00:39:42,093 --> 00:39:43,803
(VOICE SHAKING) Shit.

521
00:39:44,512 --> 00:39:45,513
I almost bought that.

522
00:39:47,890 --> 00:39:49,392
Man, do you ever lighten up?

523
00:39:49,475 --> 00:39:50,560
Nope.

524
00:39:50,643 --> 00:39:52,728
- Mm-mmm.
- (CHUCKLES)

525
00:39:56,524 --> 00:39:58,276
Hey, why don't you clean up? There's, um...

526
00:39:59,860 --> 00:40:01,237
Somethin' I wanna show you.

527
00:40:06,075 --> 00:40:08,286
So, uh, where we going?

528
00:40:12,373 --> 00:40:14,333
( INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

529
00:40:36,772 --> 00:40:38,608
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

530
00:41:09,096 --> 00:41:12,558
Now, they'll never forget
what you did for this country.

531
00:41:14,226 --> 00:41:15,603
Never.

532
00:41:33,579 --> 00:41:35,581
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

533
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:46,926
Oh! There he is!

534
00:41:51,263 --> 00:41:52,390
Where is everybody?

535
00:44:51,068 --> 00:44:53,737
SENATOR: On behalf of
the United States Intelligence Community,

536
00:44:53,821 --> 00:44:56,866
I'd like to offer you
and your family our sincerest apologies.

537
00:44:58,075 --> 00:45:01,704
The Carter name has always been
synonymous with service and trust.

538
00:45:02,204 --> 00:45:03,914
Today, we begin to set things right.

539
00:45:03,998 --> 00:45:07,042
We begin to repay
some of the debt that is owed to you.

540
00:45:08,669 --> 00:45:10,129
Thank you, Senator.

541
00:45:10,212 --> 00:45:12,882
I've been waiting
to hear those words for a long time.

542
00:45:13,757 --> 00:45:15,926
And we'd like to offer you a full pardon.

543
00:45:16,844 --> 00:45:19,096
There may be
an opening in your old division.

544
00:45:19,972 --> 00:45:22,016
Is that something you'd be interested in?

545
00:45:23,517 --> 00:45:25,060
It would be my honor.

546
00:45:26,687 --> 00:45:28,188
Welcome home, Agent Carter.

547
00:45:29,315 --> 00:45:30,858
(CLAPPING)

548
00:45:35,195 --> 00:45:36,697
( INDISTINCT MURMURING)

549
00:45:44,204 --> 00:45:45,706
(LINE RINGING)

550
00:45:47,791 --> 00:45:49,335
Start lining up our buyers.

551
00:45:49,418 --> 00:45:51,295
Super Soldiers might be off the menu,

552
00:45:51,378 --> 00:45:56,050
but we're about to have full access
to government secrets, prototype weapons,

553
00:45:56,133 --> 00:45:57,426
you name it.

554
00:45:57,509 --> 00:45:58,886
Should be something for everyone.

555
00:46:07,770 --> 00:46:11,148
(MUSIC PLAYING)

